Find the Largest of Three Numbers
•	Problem: Write a C program to find the largest of three numbers using an if-else statement.
•	Hint: Use nested if-else conditions to compare the numbers.

Program
~~~~~~~
#include <stdio.h>
#include <string.h>
int main()
{
    printf("\n~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~");
    printf("\nRitheesh.D\n1-year CSBS");
    printf("\n~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~");
    int num1,num2,num3,largest;
    printf("\nenter the first number");
    scanf("%d",&num1);
    printf("\nenter the second number");
    scanf("%d",&num2);
    printf("\nenter the third number");
    scanf("%d",&num3);
    if(num1>num2&&num1>num3)
    {
        largest = num1;
    }
    else if(num2>num1&&num2>num3)
    {
        largest = num2;
    }
    else
    {
        largest = num3;
    }
    printf("the largest number is %d\n",largest);
    return 0;
    
}
Output
~~~~~~
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Ritheesh.D
1-year CSBS
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
enter the first number6

enter the second number66

enter the third number99
the largest number is 99

