Vowel or Consonant Check
•	Problem: Write a C program to check whether a given character is a vowel or a consonant using a switch statement.
•	Hint: Use the switch case to match the character with vowels (a, e, i, o, u).

Program
~~~~~~~

#include <stdio.h>

int main()
{
 printf("---------------------------");
 printf("\n Program by: PUVITHA V YEAR B.TECH.CSBS");
 printf("-------------------------\n");
    char ch;
    printf("enter a character: ");
    scanf("%c",&ch);
    if(ch=='a'||ch=='e'||ch=='i'||ch=='o'||ch=='u'||ch=='A'||ch=='E'||ch=='I'||ch=='O'||ch=='U')
   {     
       printf("%c is a vowel\n",ch); 
   }
        else
        {
         printf("%c is a consonant\n",ch);
        }
     return 0;
}
Output
~~~~~~
---------------------------
 Program by: PUVITHA V YEAR B.TECH.CSBS
-------------------------
enter a character: t
t is a consonant
enter a character: i
i is a vowel

