Grade Assignment Based on Marks
•	Problem: Write a C program that takes marks as input and assigns a grade based on the following conditions:
o	90-100: Grade A
o	80-89: Grade B
o	70-79: Grade C
o	60-69: Grade D
o	Below 60: Grade F
•	Hint: Use if-else if conditions to handle the grading.


Program
~~~~~~~
#include <stdio.h>
#include <string.h>
int main()
{
    printf("~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~");
    printf("\nprogram BY RITHEESH D I-YEAR CSBS");
    printf("\n~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~");
    int mark;
    printf("enter the marks :");
    scanf("%d",&mark);
    if(mark>=90&&mark<=100)
    {
        printf("grade = A");
    }
    else if(mark>=80&&mark>=89)
    {
        printf("grade = B");
    }
    else if(mark>=60&&mark<=79)
    {
        printf("grade = 'C'");
    }
    else
    {
        printf("grade = 'D'");
    }
    
    return 0;
}
Output
~~~~~~
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
program BY RITHEESH D I-YEAR CSBS
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
enter the marks :99
grade = A

